  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Caroline Weston discusses her school, the Chapman children, Henry G. Chapman&apos;s health and a long breathing tube designed to cure tuberculosis. She talks about a board meeting and a disagreement between Mrs. Lydia Maria Child and William L. Garrison. She mentions John A. Collins. She reports on family members and their activities. Caroline said: &quot;Weld came to tell Henry about the earthquake&quot; (which seems to have been in Haiti). Caroline Weston tells of the experiences of the ship &quot;Dirago.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
